Description: Model cylinder jar of limestone: solid except for a very slight depression in the top, with a flat base and concave sides. The rim is roughly shaped and is rather irregular in level. The vase is decorated with wavy lines of red paint, running from the base up the sides and over the top.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tomb of Qaa, tomb Q.20 subsidiary burial
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, 15, 28, pl.XXXVIII, 5-6.
